#: ../../../release_details/9.6/add-usd-exporter.md:1
msgid "New USD exporter added"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/add-usd-exporter.md:3
msgid ""
"`vtkUSDExporter` is a new class that exports VTK scenes to Universal Scene "
"Description (USD) files (.usd, .usda (ASCII), and .usdc (binary)). It is "
"part of a new `vtk::IOUSD` module that depends on [OpenUSD](https://github."
"com/PixarAnimationStudios/OpenUSD) to write USD files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/add-usd-exporter.md:5
msgid ""
"The `vtkUSDExporter` class supports exporting the following scene elements:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/add-usd-exporter.md:6
msgid ""
"Surface polygonal geometry (verts and lines are not supported in USD) "
"including point normals if available, cell normals otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/add-usd-exporter.md:8
msgid ""
"Color mapped surfaces through export of color map textures and texture "
"coordinates on surfaces."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/add-usd-exporter.md:10
msgid "Directional lights."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/add-usd-exporter.md:11
msgid ""
"The current camera, including position and direction. Field of view is hard-"
"coded for now."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/add-usd-exporter.md:13
msgid "Actor transforms are exported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/add-usd-exporter.md:14
msgid ""
"Solid colored surfaces are exported, including physically-based rendering "
"(PBR) properties supported by the USD format when PBR is enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/add-usd-exporter.md:17
msgid ""
"3D widgets that are subclasses of `vtkWidgetRepresentation` are not exported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/add-usd-exporter.md:19
msgid "All surfaces from composite poly data are exported."
msgstr ""
